---

layout: recipe
title: Breaded Chicken Cutlets
image: breaded-chicken-cutlets.jpg
tags: dinner
recipeYield: 2

ingredients:
- 1/2 cup panko bread crumbs
- 1 tsp chili powder 
- 1 chicken breast
- 2 tbsp sour cream
- 1/4 cup monterey jack cheese
- 1 tbsp southwest spice

directions:
- Preheat oven to 425Â°F
- In a small bowl, combine panko, monterey jack, a drizzle of olive oil, 1/2 tsp of chili powder, 1 tsp of southwest spice, salt and pepper
- Butterfly chicken breast and pat dry
- Season both sides with salt and pepper
- Set chicken on baking sheet covered in foil
- Brush top of chicken with sour cream
- Coat with pank mixture, pushing firmly to adhere.
- Drizzle chicken with olive oil
- Bake until chicken is browned and cooked through, 15-18 minutes

components:
- Southwest Spice Blend

---
Good with side of mashed potatoes and roasted vegetables
